      "id": "PopularPost344649",
      "post_content": "The rules for this seem a bit twisted to me, for these reasons (correct me if I am wrong because I guess I must be)  \n  \nTo cast a spell,These are the first two steps  \n 1. Declare you are casting it (see point 1) and put it on the stack  \n 2. Announce mode choice  \n  \nTo put it on the stack at instant speed would require having already decided to pay 2 more to cast it, but you can't decide to pay 2 more to cast it until step 2 (when it's already on the stack).  \n  \n307.1. A player who has priority may cast a sorcery card from his or her hand during a main phase of  \nhis or her turn when the stack is empty. Casting a sorcery as a spell uses the stack. (See rule 601,  \n\u201cCasting Spells.\u201d)  \n  \n601.2b \"...If the spell has alternative or additional costs that will be paid as it\u2019s being cast such as  \nbuyback or kicker costs (see rules 117.8 and 117.9), the player announces his or her intentions  \nto pay any or all of those costs (see rule 601.2e)...\"  \n  \nThe way I'm reading the card seems to suggest that you pay for t... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "thought_jar",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost344649\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">The rules for this seem a bit twisted to me, for these reasons (correct me if I am wrong because I guess I must be)<br/><br/>To cast a spell,These are the first two steps<br/>  1. Declare you are casting it (see point 1) and put it on the stack<br/>  2. Announce mode choice<br/><br/>To put it on the stack at instant speed would require having already decided to pay 2 more to cast it, but you can't decide to pay 2 more to cast it until step 2 (when it's already on the stack).<br/><br/>307.1. A player who has priority may cast a sorcery card from his or her hand during a main phase of<br/>his or her turn when the stack is empty. Casting a sorcery as a spell uses the stack. (See rule 601,<br/>\u201cCasting Spells.\u201d)<br/><br/>601.2b \"...If the spell has alternative or additional costs that will be paid as it\u2019s being cast such as<br/>buyback or kicker costs (see rules 117.8 and 117.9), the player announces his or her intentions<br/>to pay any or all of those costs (see rule 601.2e)...\"<br/><br/>The way I'm reading the card seems to suggest that you pay for t... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 344649)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '344649'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div cla